The inspiration behind this video: 

After Mission: Impossible - The Final Reckoning's new trailer, I've got a theory that Ilsa Faust is alive, after all, based on one teased scene. From the moment that Ilsa Faust died in Mission: Impossible - Dead Reckoning, theories about the possibility of her still being alive started. The seventh film in the franchise made the death of Rebecca Ferguson's character quite convincing, and that also created a lot of heartbreak for viewers who wanted to see Ilsa's story continue. That left me and anyone else wanting her back to look for any possible way it could happen.

Rebecca Ferguson isn't part of Mission: Impossible - The Final Reckoning's cast list officially, and there's been no definitive tease that she's in the film. I'd mostly given up on the idea that Ilsa would return in any meaningful fashion in the potential franchise conclusion. Yet, that's changed with Mission: Impossible - The Final Reckoning's full trailer. There's not a scene in the trailer that directly references or shows Ferguson's character in full, but one moment makes me believe that Ilsa Faust is alive and part of a major subplot. Better yet, it would work with Dead Reckoning's story.
